<doc f='llvm/clang/lib/Lex/Lexer.cpp' l='2470'>/// We have just read from input the / and * characters that started a comment.
/// Read until we find the * and / characters that terminate the comment.
/// Note that we don&apos;t bother decoding trigraphs or escaped newlines in block
/// comments, because they cannot cause the comment to end.  The only thing
/// that can happen is the comment could end with an escaped newline between
/// the terminating * and /.
///
/// If we&apos;re in KeepCommentMode or any CommentHandler has inserted
/// some tokens, this will store the first token and return true.</doc>
